SIMPLE: striker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Striker
<hw>Strik"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, strikes; specifically, a blacksmith's helper who wields
the sledge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A harpoon; also, a harpooner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wherever we come to an anchor, we always send out our
<qex>strikers</qex>, and put out hooks and lines overboard, to try
fish.</q> <rj><qau>Dampier.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A wencher; a lewd man.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Massinger.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A workman who is on a strike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A blackmailer in politics; also, one whose political
influence can be bought.</def> <mark>[Political Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strike zone</ent>⟦br⟧
